 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.5","title":"fcp.workspace-events: Google Workspace Events connector plus Pub/Sub lifecycle management","description":"Implement the Google Workspace Events connector on top of the shared Google platform, including explicit provisioning and lifecycle handling for Workspace subscriptions and Pub/Sub-backed delivery paths.","design":"Workspace Events is the event-driven keystone of the Google Workspace ecosystem. Unlike simpler CRUD services, it spans API operations plus external Pub/Sub resources and renewal/reactivation workflows. The connector should therefore use the shared substrate for generic Google mechanics but expect a larger handwritten overlay for subscription lifecycle, event consumption, and provisioning integration.","acceptance_criteria":"- Subscription and reactivation surfaces are defined and policy-mapped.\n- Pub/Sub lifecycle requirements are documented and integrated with provisioning automation.\n- Event payload semantics are explicit enough for agent-facing introspection and tests.","notes":"This connector is strategically important because it unlocks reactive Google workflows instead of limiting the platform to polling and request/response automation.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:31:18.279048Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-03-06T07:40:18.348907Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["connectors","events","fcp2","google","workspace"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.5","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.1.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:40:16.940992Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.5","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.1.8.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:40:17.057933Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.5","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.2.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:31:27.290238Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.5","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:31:18.279048Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":899,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.5","author":"Jeff Emanuel","text":"Workspace Events was explicitly called out in the memo as one of the best candidates for thin high-value helpers and provisioning integration. It is not just another CRUD connector; it spans subscriptions, renew/reactivate flows, and Pub/Sub lifecycle management, which is why it now depends on the helper-policy and provisioning-detail beads as well as the overall migration acceptance gate.","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:40:18Z"}]}
 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.6","title":"fcp.people: Google People/Contacts connector via the shared discovery-pinned substrate","description":"Implement the Google People/Contacts connector using the shared Google platform, with careful privacy and approval treatment around personal data access and mutation.","design":"People is mechanically well-suited to the shared platform, but the policy layer matters more than usual because the data is often personal and sensitive. The connector should make capability and approval boundaries especially explicit for contact mutation and profile reads.","acceptance_criteria":"- Core People operations are generator-backed.\n- Privacy-sensitive reads and writes are mapped clearly into FCP approval/risk semantics.\n- The connector is usable without hiding policy-sensitive behavior behind convenience wrappers.","notes":"People is lower priority than Drive/Docs/Sheets/Chat, but important for personal-assistant and coordination workflows.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:31:18.512657Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-03-06T07:31:27.401570Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["connectors","fcp2","google","people","workspace"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.6","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.2.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:31:27.401537Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.6","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:31:18.512657Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.7","title":"fcp.admin-reports: Google Workspace Admin Reports connector via the shared discovery-pinned substrate","description":"Implement the Google Workspace Admin Reports connector using the shared Google platform, with explicit treatment of admin-only scopes, domain-admin environments, and audit/reporting semantics.","design":"Admin Reports is valuable because it exposes audit logs and usage reports, but it also represents the sharp edge of Google admin-only scope behavior. The connector should therefore be a proving ground for how the shared platform handles admin-only scopes, restricted environments, and domain-specific deployment guidance without pretending every Google connector targets the same user context.","acceptance_criteria":"- Admin-only scope behavior is documented and policy-mapped.\n- Generated baseline operations are combined with explicit deployment and approval guidance.\n- The connector's assumptions about domain-admin context are obvious to operators and agents.","notes":"This connector is intentionally included early in the wave because it forces the platform to handle the reality that not all Google APIs are personal-user friendly.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:31:18.836160Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-03-06T07:31:27.512682Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["admin","connectors","fcp2","google","workspace"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.7","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.2.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:31:27.512649Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3.7","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-lszk.45.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:31:18.836160Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
